Wrangling data¶

Converting CombinedCode to Module Title¶

df_numbers only shows the size of each class against with module code, however we work with the Module Title, hence lets ammend df_number such that it works with the module title too.

In [ ]:
df = df_pan[['MODULE_TITLE', 'CombinedCode']].drop_duplicates(subset=['CombinedCode'])
keys = list(df.CombinedCode)
values = list(df.MODULE_TITLE)
dict_numbers = dict(zip(keys, values))
df_numbers['MODULE_TITLE'] = df_numbers['CombinedCode'].map(dict_numbers)
df_numbers.drop(columns='CombinedCode', inplace=True)

Now let us convert the LastView time into binary

  • 1 : Lecture last viewed before the end of term 2
  • 0 : Lecture last viewed after term 2
In [ ]:
# 18-19 academic year
spring19_end = datetime.date(year=2019,month=3,day=18)

# 19-20 academic year
spring20_end = datetime.date(year=2020,month=3,day=16)

# 20-21 academic year
spring21_end = datetime.date(year=2021,month=3,day=26)


### 18-19
year_cond = (df_pan['ACAD_YEAR'] == 2018)
lectures19 = (year_cond) & (df_pan['LastViewTime'] <= spring19_end)
exams19 = (year_cond) & (df_pan['LastViewTime'] > spring19_end) 
### 19-20
year_cond = (df_pan['ACAD_YEAR'] == 2019)
lectures20 = (year_cond) & (df_pan['LastViewTime'] <= spring20_end)
exams20 = (year_cond) & (df_pan['LastViewTime'] > spring20_end)


### 20-21
year_cond = (df_pan['ACAD_YEAR'] == 2020)
lectures21 = (year_cond) & (df_pan['LastViewTime'] <= spring21_end)
exams21 = (year_cond) & (df_pan['LastViewTime'] > spring21_end)



df_pan.loc[lectures19 | lectures20 | lectures21, 'LastViewTime'] = 1
df_pan.loc[exams19 | exams20 | exams21, 'LastViewTime'] = 0

# Convert to float to allow arithmetic to be performed
df_pan['LastViewTime'] = pd.to_numeric(df_pan['LastViewTime'], downcast='float') 
df_pan.LastViewTime.value_counts()

Let us create a dictionary assigning all year one modules to 1, year 2 modules to to and year 3/4 modules to 3. And then apply it creating a new column: year.

In [ ]:
yr1 = ['An Introduction to Applied Mathematics',
       'Analysis 1',
       'Calculus and Applications',
       'Introduction to Computation',
       'Introduction to University Mathematics',
       'Linear Algebra and Groups',
       'Probability and Statistics',
       'Algebra 1',
       'Foundations of Analysis',
       'Geometry and Linear Algebra',
       'Probability and Statistics 1',
       'Mathematical Computation',
       ]
yr2 = ['Analysis 2',
       'Linear Algebra and Numerical Analysis',
       'Multivariable Calculus and Differential Equations',
       'Network Science',
       'Partial Differential Equations in Action: Modelling in Applied Mathematics',
       'Probability for Statistics',
       'Algebra 2',
       'Differential Equations',
       'Introduction to Numerical Analysis',
       'Multivariable Calculus',
       'Probability and Statistics 2',
       'Real Analysis',
       'Statistical Modelling 1',
       'Lebesgue Measure and Integration',
       'Groups and Rings',
       ]
yr3 = all_modules - set(yr2) - set(yr1)

dict_year = dict.fromkeys(yr1, 1)
dict_year.update(dict.fromkeys(yr2, 2))
dict_year.update(dict.fromkeys(yr3, 3))
df['year'] = df['MODULE_TITLE'].map(dict_year)

Adding whether modules are compulsory¶

# FOR df_all
cols = ['AvgViewsAndDownloads',
 'PercentCompleted',
 'PropTermTimeLastView',
 'HoursInBbCourse'] # Columns to check for outliers

# Data is NOT an outlier if it is a NAN or if it achieves a |zscore| of less than 3
cond_kept = ((df_all[cols].isna()) | (np.abs(stats.zscore(df_all[cols], nan_policy='omit')) < 3))

#Q1 = df_all[cols].quantile(0.25)
#Q3 = df_all[cols].quantile(0.75)
#IQR = Q3 - Q1
#cond_kept = (df_all[cols].isna()) | ((df_all[cols] >= (Q1 - 1.5*IQR)) & (df_all[cols] <= (Q3 + 1.5*IQR)))



cond_all = cond_kept.all(axis=1)
outliers = df_all[~cond_all]
percent_outliers = 1 - sum(cond_all)/len(df_all.index)
percent_outliers *= 100

print(percent_outliers, '% outliers')
print(len(outliers.index), 'num outliers')
df_all = df_all.loc[cond_all] # Update df_all

dpi = 600
lw = 1
cut = 0
font_size=18

sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(21, 7)})
sns.set_theme(style="whitegrid")
covariates = ['AvgViewsAndDownloads',
              'MinutesDelivered',
              'PercentCompleted',
              'PropTermTimeLastView',
              'HoursInBbCourse',
              ]
covariate_names = ['Average Views',
              'Minutes Delivered per person',
              'Percent Completed',
              'Proportion of videos last viewed in term time',
              'Hours In Blackboard',
              ]
for i in range(len(covariates)):
  covariate = covariates[i]
  covariate_name = covariate_names[i]


  sns.violinplot(data=df, x='ACAD_YEAR', y=covariate, palette="Pastel1", linewidth=lw, cut=cut)
  plt.xticks([0, 1, 2], ['18-19', '19-20', '20-21'])
  plt.xlabel('Academic Year')
  plt.ylabel(covariate_name)
  title = 'Violin plot of ' + covariate_name + ' by Academic Year'
  plt.title(title, fontdict = {'fontsize' : font_size})
  name = '/content/drive/MyDrive/student_shapers_data/saves/violin_plots/' + covariate + '_violinplot.pdf'
  plt.savefig(name, dpi=dpi)
  plt.show()

  sns.violinplot(x='ACAD_YEAR', y=covariate, hue='year', data=df, palette="Pastel1", linewidth=lw, cut=cut)
  plt.xticks([0, 1, 2], ['18-19', '19-20', '20-21'])
  plt.xlabel('Academic Year')
  plt.legend(title = 'Year')
  plt.ylabel(covariate_name)
  title = 'Violin plot of ' + covariate_name + ' by Academic Year, year group'
  plt.title(title, fontdict = {'fontsize' : font_size})
  name = '/content/drive/MyDrive/student_shapers_data/saves/violin_plots/' + covariate + '_violinplot_by_year.pdf'
  plt.savefig(name, dpi=dpi)
  plt.show()

  sns.violinplot(x='ACAD_YEAR', y=covariate, hue='compulsory', data=df, palette="Pastel1", linewidth=lw, cut=cut)
  plt.xticks([0, 1, 2], ['18-19', '19-20', '20-21'])
  plt.xlabel('Academic Year')
  handles, labels = plt.gca().get_legend_handles_labels()
  labels = ['Compulsory' if x == '1' else 'Elective' for x in labels]
  plt.legend(handles, labels)
  plt.ylabel(covariate_name)
  title = 'Violin plot of ' + covariate_name + ' by Academic Year, compulsory modules'
  plt.title(title, fontdict = {'fontsize' : font_size})
  name = '/content/drive/MyDrive/student_shapers_data/saves/violin_plots/' + covariate + '_violinplot_by_comp.pdf'
  plt.savefig(name, dpi=dpi)
  plt.show()

cols = [x for x in cols if x != 'Id']

### iqr method
Q1 = df_pia[cols].quantile(0.25)
Q3 = df_pia[cols].quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1
cond_kept = (df_pia[cols].isna()) | ((df_pia[cols] >= (Q1 - 1.5 * IQR)) & (df_pia[cols] <= (Q3 + 1.5 * IQR)))
cond_all = cond_kept.all(axis=1)
outliers = df_pia[~cond_all]
percent_outliers = len(outliers.index)/len(df_pia.index)
percent_outliers *= 100


print('Outliers by using IQR')
print(percent_outliers, '% outliers')
print(len(outliers.index), 'num outliers')
print('_'*50)
print('_'*50)



### zscore method
# Data is NOT an outlier if it is a NAN or if it achieves a |zscore| of less than 3
cond_kept = ((df_pia[cols].isna()) | (np.abs(stats.zscore(df_pia[cols], nan_policy='omit')) < 3))
cond_all = cond_kept.all(axis=1)
outliers = df_pia[~cond_all]
percent_outliers = len(outliers.index)/len(df_pia.index)
percent_outliers *= 100

#df_pia = df_pia.loc[cond_all] # Update df

print(percent_outliers, '% outliers')
print(len(outliers.index), 'num outliers')

ten = ['Analysis 1', 'Calculus and Applications', 'Linear Algebra and Groups', 'Probability and Statistics']
y1five = [ 'An Introduction to Applied Mathematics', 'Introduction to Computation', 'Introduction to University Mathematics']

def f(row):
    if row['MODULE_TITLE'] in (ten + y2comp):
        val = 1
    elif row['MODULE_TITLE'] in (oldy1comp + oldy2comp + y2elec + y1five):
        val = 2
    else:
        val = 4/3
    return val

dfw['Weight'] = dfw.apply(f, axis=1)
